('chunk_c2f7465690dc1c1517','file_162fce15bbe62004d5','geography.md','Cross-Subject Connections','- **Biology:** Adaptation, food chains/webs, nutrient cycling, photosynthesis, biodiversity and conservation directly overlap with biome study; permafrost thaw links to the carbon and methane cycles.
- **Chemistry:** The carbon cycle, greenhouse gases and combustion of fossil fuels, soil chemistry (nutrients, pH, salinisation), water treatment and desalination, and materials in the recycling/circular economy.
- **History:** Colonialism and its role in the North–South divide and the "resource curse"; the Industrial Revolution and fossil-fuel dependence; the 1930s Dust Bowl; the displacement of indigenous peoples; the history of international cooperation (UN, Earth Summit 1992, Paris 2015).
- **Physics (extension):** Energy transfer and efficiency, how solar/wind/hydro generate electricity, and heat/pressure in the atmospheric circulation that drives pressure belts.

